-- Copper Futures Climb in New York, Erasing Earlier Drop of as Much as 0.8%
-- Patrick McKiernan
-- 2010-07-14T15:52:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/copper-futures-climb-in-new-york-erasing-earlier-drop-of-as-much-as-0-8-.html

          
          
             Copper futures for September
delivery rose 3.05 cents, or 1 percent, to $3.048 a pound at
11:52 a.m. on the Comex in New York. Earlier, the metal dropped
as much as 0.8 percent.  
          
          


  


        